      "side": 1,
      "message": "Masking with 0x3f would not be equivalent here. It would alias out-of-range protocol/type values back into [0..63], while this fix intentionally maps them to 0 to avoid false matches. I also checked codegen: both x86_64 and AArch64 lower the guarded form to a branch-free conditional select/move at -O3 (cmov on x86, csel on arm64), so I’d prefer to keep the explicit range check.",
